OL,3,CStatue 'knocked off plinth' in storm
OL,4,Creturns to cemetery four years later
OL,6,FExcited to have the monument back, Ann
OL,7,FFiddler, the CEO of Arnos Vale
OL,8,FCemetery Trust, said: "She was gone
OL,9,Ffrom Arnos Vale for over a year. Bath
OL,10,FCollege very kindly used it as a bit
OL,11,Fof a training piece although some of
OL,12,Fthe key leads over there got quite
OL,13,Finvolved.
OL,15,F"They very kindly did this for free.
OL,16,FOf course, there's the cost of the
OL,17,Fscaffolding and people's time, which
OL,18,Fwe've had donations through for, which
OL,19,Fwas absolutely marvellous. But we were
OL,20,Fable to do this very cost-effectively."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
