OL,3,CStatue 'knocked off plinth' in storm
OL,4,Creturns to cemetery four years later
OL,6,FNot much is known of Anne Neilson and
OL,7,Fher relatives, whose names are on the
OL,8,Fplinth below the Hope Monument. Sadly,
OL,9,Fthe words are fading away after more
OL,10,Fthan a hundred years of wear and tear
OL,11,Fand the grave itself is crumbling.
OL,13,FYou can visit Hope at the Combe Bottom
OL,14,Farea of Arnos Vale, close to the grave
OL,15,Fof the educational reformer Mary
OL,16,FCarpenter who died in 1877. She
OL,17,Ffounded ragged schools for poor
OL,18,Fchildren and young offenders in
OL,19,FBristol.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/6
